# Logs
logs
*.log
npm-debug.log*
yarn-debug.log*
yarn-error.log*
pnpm-debug.log*
lerna-debug.log*

node_modules
# Root frontend build output only — the installer's hand-written UI (installer/dist)
# is source and IS tracked.
/dist
/dist-ssr
*.local

# Rust build output — NEVER committed. The whole point is that users clone clean
# source and compile it on their own machine, so no build data ships in the repo.
**/target/

# Installer build artifacts + any bundled/prebuilt binaries. The installer is
# compiled from installer/src; it never embeds a prebuilt app exe.
installer/resources/
*-setup.exe

# Tauri updater signing keys — NEVER commit the private key.
.tauri-signing/

# Per-user Claude Code settings (local, not for the public repo).
.claude/settings.local.json

# Internal release runbook — keep the signing/release process private.
RELEASING.md

# App data / secrets must NEVER be committed. The app keeps all user data in the OS
# app-data dir + keychain (never the repo); these are a defensive backstop in case a
# DB / env / key file is ever dropped into the working tree during development.
*.db
*.db-*
*.sqlite
*.sqlite3
.env
.env.*
*.pem
*.p12
*.key

# At-rest-encryption working/backup artifacts — these can hold PLAINTEXT user data and must
# never be committed if one ever lands in the working tree during development.
*.bak
*.migsnap
db.lock.json
xconsole-unencrypted-backup-*.db

# Editor directories and files
.vscode/*
!.vscode/extensions.json
.idea
.DS_Store
*.suo
*.ntvs*
*.njsproj
*.sln
*.sw?
